Citadel Capital Gains in Cairo as Unit Chosen to Operate Plant

-- B y   A h m e d   A   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-05-25T09:49:19Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-25/citadel-capital-gains-in-cairo-as-unit-chosen-to-operate-plant.html
Citadel Capital SAE rose for the
first time in four days after a unit of the Cairo-based private
equity firm signed an agreement to operate a cement plant for
 South Valley Cement. (SVCE)   The shares advanced 2.3 percent to 5 Egyptian pounds at
11:20 a.m. in Cairo. South Valley shares rose as much as 1.8
percent to 4.55 pounds.  South Valley said yesterday it signed an agreement with
Citadel unit  Arab Swiss Engineering Co. , or Asec Cement, for the
management and operation of a cement plant in the southern
Egyptian province of Beni Suef.  To contact the reporter on this story:
{Ahmed A Namatalla} in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Claudia Maedler at 
 cmaedler@bloomberg.net  